Abstract: The relevance of paradigms focusing on rational and sociopolitical power in strategic decision-making is explored among three country clusters. The predictive validity of a model incorporating political and rational sources of power is established across the clusters. Moreover, country clusters appear to moderate the power relationships.&copy; 1987 JIBS. Journal of International Business Studies (1987) 18, 1&ndash;14
